<seg id=1> Guangxi Builds Traffic and Water Transportation Infrastructure by Foreign Capital of 150 Million US Dollars </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, March 14 (by Journalist Lu Hankui) - The traffic department of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region reveals that up to now, Guangxi has built traffic and water transportation infrastructure by utilization foreign loan of totally 150 million US dollars from World Bank, Asian Bank, Netherland and Korea etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In recent years, China has speeded up the construction of major access from great Southwest area to the sea through Guangxi. </seg>
<seg id=4> In order to solve the problem of insufficient fund, and open wider to the outside world, Guangxi strengthened its introduction and utilization of foreign capitals. </seg>
<seg id=5> The second phase of Xijiang River Transportation hub, with total investment of over 200 million yuan Renminbi, utilized Word Bank loan of 80 million US dollars. Up to now, its major earthwork has been finished by 80%, and concrete pouring finished by 50%. </seg>
<seg id=6> The second phase project of Fangcheng Gang port (including the express highway from Qinzhou city to Fangcheng Gang city) utilized Asian Development Bank loan of 52 million US dollars. It is estimated that this express highway will be completed and put into use in the second half of this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> North Sea port auxiliary facilities construction project utilized Korean government loan of 10 million US dollars. </seg>
<seg id=8> Qinzhou port auxiliary facilities construction project utilized Netherland government loan of 13 million US dollars. </seg>
<seg id=9> All these construction projects are smoothly under way. </seg>
</p>
